                    <h2>Red Hat JBoss BPM Suite</h2>
                    <h3>Online Workshop</h3>
                    This workshop will teach you how to build a business process for a company that wants
                    to automate its human resource (HR) employee awards program.
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Red Hat JBoss BPM Suite</h2>
                    <h3>Online Workshop</h3>
                    This process has been initially scoped to have a single user task (human involvement),
                    which will be the assigned to the <code>manager</code> group in the company. This role
                    is held by all HR department employees, who have to approve or reject rewards submissions.
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Red Hat JBoss BPM Suite</h2>
                    <h3>Online Workshop</h3>
                    After a reward is evaluated by HR, the process must add an entry into the employees
                    personnel file and send a notification email. This must be done for the case where
                    the reward is approved and where it is rejected.
                </section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Red Hat JBoss BPM Suite</h2>
                    <h3>Online Workshop</h3>
